==English==
{{rfv}}
Frenemy, n., plural frenemies. A neologism which is a blending of "friend" and "enemy". Refers to someone who pretends to be your friend, but is really your enemy. Was used as the title of a Sex in the City episode in 2000; however, some people had heard it earlier than that. Due to the obviousness of this coinage, and the real social phenomena it representeds (at least in certain situations, most notably high schools), it seems not unlikely it has been the subject of multiple independent inventions.